race.description: Elders Killara Feedlot F&M Benchmark 58 Handicap
race.comment: YES YES BOSS (8) enjoyed the return to 1000m last start when a close fourth at big odds in a Muswellbrook Class 1. Likes to bowl along in front so with just 55kgs after the claim in this easier race she will be very tough to catch. KANTISHNA (2) made it four minor placings on the bounce when she loomed up to win but found one a little better over this trip at Muswellbrook last time out. Has her share of weight but is still going well deep into the prep and should be competitive again. THIS ONE TIME (3) returns from a 20-week spell. Led but knocked up when resuming from a much longer break last prep in a hot form race over 900m, then won two on the bounce. Expect her to be a lot more forward for this return. SIMPLY BETTER (4) has been racing well in 1100m races of late. Four-time winner at 1000m so this is right in her wheelhouse. Lightly raced five-year-old BROKEN WINGS (7) has trialled twice and should be ready to run well off a 269-day break.
